The '''Qel-Droma robes''' were created as a gift for [[Cay Qel-Droma]] during the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Sith War]]. Cay wore them when he was murdered by his brother [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma]] who had fallen to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. The robes were passed on to Cay and Ulic's cousin [[Duron Qel-Droma]], but disappeared shortly after the [[Great Hunt (Jedi)|Great Hunt]] along with Duron himself. Later, during the [[Jedi Civil War]], shortly after slaying the [[Terentatek/Legends|Terentatek]] that killed [[Duron Qel-Droma]], [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] and his companions found his robes in a cave on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], along with Duron's skeletal remains.

It was said that only those who are true to the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side of the Force]] could wear the robes. Imbued with the light side, the robes would enhance the wisdom and protection of the wearer.

In the moments before his death, Duron Qel-Droma experienced a vision of the redeemed Revan finding his remains and donning these robes, then defeating a [[Darth Malak|disfigured Sith]].

==Behind the scenes==
As it first appeared, the robe was a simple cape in a red color that didn't differ much from previous depictions of [[Cay Qel-Droma]]. However, in ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'', the robe uses the same model as the generic Jedi robe, and can only be worn by a light-sided Jedi character (the player character if light side options are chosen, [[Bastila Shan|Bastila]] and [[Juhani]]). Its most recent appearance was in [[Shadows and Light]], drawn by [[Dustin Weaver]]. In the comic, it again shares the red tint as originally depicted.

